It is the star of New York's skyline.

Now, for a cool $1 billion, it could be yours.

The Empire State Building is going up for sale.

No longer the world's tallest, but still the most iconic, the 102-storey skyscraper has been the subject of gushing poems, films and music since it emerged in 1931.

And today, in a move that has sent the market into a frenzy, reports emerged that the Malkin family, owner of the legendary art deco tower, plans to let it go.

